yde directly. Glycolaldehyde is photooxidized to glyoxal, which feeds the Radziszewski imidazole synthesis. Imidazole is alkylated with FTT-derived glycolaldehyde, then Strecker synthesis yields histidine.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_003", "rxn_005", "rxn_009", "rxn_010", "rxn_015", "rxn_016", "rxn_017"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_007", "mol_008", "mol_009", "mol_010", "mol_014", "mol_015"]}, {"pathway_id": "P5", "name": "Formate \u2192 formaldehyde \u2192 formose glycolaldehyde \u2192 erythrose \u2192 imidazole-4-acetaldehyde \u2192 Strecker", "description": "CO2 is reduced to formate then formaldehyde hydrothermally. Formaldehyde undergoes formose reaction with borate to glycolaldehyde, which self-condenses to erythrose. Erythrose reacts with ammonia to directly form imidazole-4-acetaldehyde via cyclization, bypassing free imidazole. Strecker synthesis yields histidine.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_001", "rxn_002", "rxn_008", "rxn_013", "rxn_014", "rxn_016", "rxn_017"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_003", "mol_004", "mol_008", "mol_013", "mol_014", "mol_015"]}, {"pathway_id": "P6", "name": "Fischer-Tropsch glycolaldehyde \u2192 erythrose \u2192 imidazole-4-acetaldehyde \u2192 Strecker", "description": "CO and H2 produce glycolaldehyde via FTT on magnetite. Glycolaldehyde undergoes aldol condensation to erythrose with borate stabilization. Erythrose cyclizes with ammonia to form imidazole-4-acetaldehyde directly, which undergoes Strecker synthesis to histidine.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_003", "rxn_005", "rxn_013", "rxn_014", "rxn_016", "rxn_017"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_007", "mol_008", "mol_013", "mol_014", "mol_015"]}, {"pathway_id": "P7", "name": "DAMN-imidazole \u2192 erythrose route \u2192 Strecker histidine (dual convergence)", "description": "HCN oligomerizes to DAMN which forms imidazole with formaldehyde. Simultaneously, formose glycolaldehyde condenses to erythrose. Both the erythrose-ammonia route and the imidazole-alkylation route converge on imidazole-4-acetaldehyde. Uses HCN from hydrothermal CO+NH3.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_003", "rxn_004", "rxn_007", "rxn_011", "rxn_001", "rxn_002", "rxn_008", "rxn_013", "rxn_014", "rxn_016", "rxn_017"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_006", "mol_012", "mol_010", "mol_008", "mol_013", "mol_014"]}, {"pathway_id": "P8", "name": "Formamide-imidazole \u2192 FTT glycolaldehyde alkylation \u2192 Strecker", "description": "HCN is hydrated to formamide (UV/TiO2), which condenses on phosphate minerals to form imidazole. Separately, FTT synthesis on magnetite produces glycolaldehyde. Imidazole is alkylated with FTT-glycolaldehyde to form imidazole-4-acetaldehyde. Strecker synthesis completes the route to histidine.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_003", "rxn_004", "rxn_006", "rxn_012", "rxn_005", "rxn_015", "rxn_016", "rxn_017"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_006", "mol_011", "mol_010", "mol_008", "mol_014", "mol_015"]}, {"pathway_id": "P9", "name": "Radziszewski imidazole (from formose) \u2192 erythrose-based imidazole-4-acetaldehyde \u2192 Strecker", "description": "Formaldehyde from formate reduction feeds both the formose reaction (\u2192glycolaldehyde\u2192glyoxal for Radziszewski) and aldol erythrose synthesis. Imidazole forms via Radziszewski; erythrose+NH3 independently forms imidazole-4-acetaldehyde. Two convergent routes to the Strecker precursor.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_001", "rxn_002", "rxn_008", "rxn_009", "rxn_010", "rxn_013", "rxn_014", "rxn_016", "rxn_017"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_004", "mol_008", "mol_009", "mol_010", "mol_013", "mol_014"]}, {"pathway_id": "P10", "name": "Mixed hydrothermal-surface: dual CO2 reduction routes converging on Strecker histidine", "description": "Both hydrothermal CO2 reduction routes operate simultaneously: (1) CO2\u2192formate\u2192formaldehyde provides formaldehyde for Radziszewski and formose; (2) CO2\u2192CO\u2192HCN provides cyanide for Strecker and DAMN route. These converge via imidazole-4-acetaldehyde formation through either